I will say it again and again: click up takes these various cases into account and provides the ability to organize and focus to your role not just some fictional structure someone came up with

Make it easy for executives? Your individual contributors lose context and provide empty information. Make it report driven? Misses the pain and frustration of maintaining workflow. Focus on managers delegating work? Lose sight of the overall picture
So often I see someone with a great idea on software that only focuses on one audience member of the software rather than the multitude of users who will interact

PjM software should be about the whole picture. People have to use it daily to easily understand their workload, leaders need easy to access reports to get a pulse on status and blockers, teams need to spread information relative to their tasks...

The best project management software you will use is not the one you build yourself. Unless you helped build @clickup . Only then Is your software the best. So many people try to reinvent pjm software and only end up making it more confusing and frustrating.

You often hear, “it’s okay to not be okay!” But also remember: “it’s okay to be okay!” No matter the state of the world, your life has meaning to itself, be where you are and experience where you are at actively. You are not an observer to your own life. You’re the participant!
I’ve opted for voice memo journaling when I’m too tired. I’m spending the morning today catching up on my written journal which gives me a chance to revisit and acknowledge my progress!

I don’t think this is an easy thing for anyone to do. But I encourage you who are like me with all that anxiety to speak out loud your permission to yourself to indulge in the good and to not wait for the bad.
It’s pretty freeing to accept life has ups and downs and I don’t have to cling to the ups in fear that they won’t come back... or sit in the downs fearing the ups are gone for good.

I think this may be one of the first times in my life and self care journey that I am allowing myself to ride the high and I am not waiting for the bottom to fall out. I don’t need to anticipate it, it will happen eventually I’m sure but I can just be happy without worrying???

So, today  I shall self soothe, self care, self love a bit and give myself the time to grieve this dynamic change... as she said, "We grieve like we love."  And god how important of a connection she was for me through so many crazy changes in my life! (6/7)

We both agreed that I should take a "therapy vacation" to give me some mental space back away from <omg new therapist search fear> and to remember that I did this work, I have these tools. it might be different, it might be a little hard, but I can do this solo for a bit! (5/7)
Finally, as we were saying "see you later!" she paused to remind me that I had done this work. That I am capable of continuing the work without her. That I may feel lonely but I am not alone! (4/7)

Even though she provided the safe space for me to learn, grow, and express myself -- I had to do the work to heal and overcome. She said she would miss me as a client because I wanted to get better, I wanted to learn, I wanted to try!(3/7)

I spent some time walking down memory lane of all the things I've conquered and worked through since I started seeing her. I was questioning if I was gay when I walked into her office! We both got a bit emotional and the thing that touched me the most was...(2/7)
